01:04:51.220 --> 01:04:52.429
Thomas Adler: in the,

533
01:04:53.650 --> 01:05:04.589
Thomas Adler: end of the 70s, early 80s, and I finished my dissertation in 79, I think my… the PhD technically is 1980.

534
01:05:04.770 --> 01:05:11.019
Thomas Adler: That I got. So, as of 1980, or the fall of 79, I was here in Lexington.

535
01:05:11.660 --> 01:05:12.630
Thomas Adler: And…

536
01:05:13.080 --> 01:05:30.940
Thomas Adler: That was a tough time for all of us, in a way, in the humanities, in the English department, regardless of which of those subgroups we represented in the English department, because at that point, humanities in general were going through a tough period.

537
01:05:31.010 --> 01:05:41.540
Thomas Adler: We were, you know, students were either going into business or computer science. They were kind of abandoning humanities, out of a sense of,

