576
01:09:31.450 --> 01:09:38.690
Thomas Adler: You don't have to sell computers, but I'm trying to create a support group to support the whole company.

577
01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:45.140
Thomas Adler: with this new thing that was happening then called desktop publishing. Now, Apple had

578
01:09:45.700 --> 01:09:48.959
Thomas Adler: pioneered desktop publishing in the Mac world.

579
01:09:49.220 --> 01:10:04.359
Thomas Adler: And it… and people in the IBM world didn't even know about it. And they certainly didn't understand the terminology of publishing at all. They didn't… they didn't know the difference between a font and a typeface, and kerning, and leading, and all these publication terms.

580
01:10:04.480 --> 01:10:09.319
Thomas Adler: And they certainly didn't know how to do any of that on a PC.

581
01:10:09.570 --> 01:10:14.950
Thomas Adler: And the software for doing it was very… on an IBM PC, was very primitive.

582
01:10:15.460 --> 01:10:21.519
Thomas Adler: But I agreed, I needed a job, and I thought I could do that, so I joined the CBM support

583
01:10:21.730 --> 01:10:22.570
